  <description type="morphology">Annuals or biennials; rhizomes none. Stems strigose (hairs appressed to ascending, 0.2–0.5 mm). Leaves: basal blades spatulate to narrowly or broadly oblanceolate, 3–15(–20) mm wide, margins usually entire, sometimes dentate, sparsely strigose to strigose-hirsute or hirsutulous. Involucres 2–4 mm, sparsely strigose (hairs terete, 0.1–0.5 mm). 2n = 18, 27, 36, 54.</description>
